            <thetext>If you want to optimize PNG without losing quality you might wanna look at PNGOUT (http://advsys.net/ken/util/pngout.htm). It&#39;s just using an optimized deflate compressor, that results in smaller files, but not changing the content at all. So you should not get blurry iamges with this.

I for myself have been using KZIP for a while and didn&#39;t have any problems at all.</thetext>
